-- Turkey’s January Electricity Consumption Rose 8.6% Year-on-Year
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-02-06T09:10:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/turkey-s-january-electricity-consumption-rose-8-6-year-on-year.html
Turkey ’s electricity consumption rose
8.6 percent, to 21.3 billion kilowatt-hours, last month compared
with January 2011, the governmen’s power transmission company
said.  Power generation was 21.4 billion kwh, up from 19.5 billion
kwh, the company said on its  website  today.  Turkey consumed 229.3 billion kwh of power in 2011, 9
percent more than in the previous year; it produced 228.4
billion kwh, up 8.1 percent, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
